comment:
This woman is an exceptionally dangerous disordered personality.  I‚Äôm pretty site some part of her was plotting to do him dirty from day one. It‚Äôs not like she can actually love another person. Johnny DEPP is a not an ego driven celebrity, he‚Äôs an exception to the rule, an empath, and an artist of rare integrity and inspiration. This chick couldn‚Äôt pull this crap on Charlie Sheen or Jude Law. God loves them, but these guys are not sensitive or open the way DEPP is and I am sure Christian Slater, Leo, and even Brad Pitt who is also uniquely gifted and human in his own right, would‚Äôve never get serious with her but if she pulled what she does with Depl they would‚Äôve bitch slapped her and thrown her out. As someone who‚Äôs familiar with the dynamic of DV I work hard to make sense of the pathology of the abuser and the abused. Blaming the prey and smearing them is a predictable pattern.  Pulling off extreme drama when the prey is vulnerable ( Depp was mourning his mom) and destroying them is also a sad aspect of these relationships. Most of us are doomed to repeat the mistakes because the predator recognizes our scars and the qualities that make us the sort of people they can harm.  It‚Äôs hard to accept it, but there are many people who are out to hut others, especially others who have qualities they don‚Äôt. Compassion, integrity, honesty, openness, empathy and true creative inspiration are not within their grasp. She can act. That‚Äôs obvious hear.  But it‚Äôs only another lie to her. To someone like  Depp it‚Äôs an endeavor that allows them to embody another, to walk in their shoes. 
Her voice reminds me of my own which really appalls me.

As a qualified nurse  that worked in Orthopaedic /A & E  minor injury clinics, the injury that Johhny Depp received was not one from punching a wall - it is called a boxer's fracture- usually an angulated fracture of the 4-5 metarcarpal shaft-a fracture which affects the bone between the knuckle and the wrist. Where the force of the impact is compensated for and the bone breaks further down the shaft of the finger and not the finger tip.
Medical doctors know this so if opinion is sought in court Amber Heard will be proved to be lying.

When the public is confronted with abusive behavior they tend to protect a real victim not doubting in this dimension about her allegations. In this case, she seems desoriented, maniac and confused about what really happened. A typical victim of domestic violence tends to believe every moment of the abuse but she seems to not being sure of what happened and sometimes seems to even not know the answer to the simplest questions. I don‚Äôt think she is telling the truths simply because she can‚Äôt even make of her mind about what happened and doesn‚Äôt seem in genuine fear but is more focused on transmitting the emotion necessary to sell her story.

comment: People are going to think I‚Äôm an idiot, but this makes me so friggin sad. Johnny Depp is a celebrity but of course this happens to everyday people all the time. Quarantine has given me too much time to think and I‚Äôve gotten into real funk over feeling sorry for myself. My husband and I were both in the army and he died when I was 30. He was such a kind person, never raised his voice to me even. I didn‚Äôt have the best life before I met him, and I was so grateful for the life we had together. I remember how often I would think ‚Äúthis is too good to be true, how did this happen?‚Äù I was so happy and felt so safe but I always thought I didn‚Äôt deserve him or the life we had. I could never shake the feeling that I was going to lose him. I didn‚Äôt believe he would cheat on me or anything like that, I never thought he would die...we were so young. I just never thought of him dying but I KNEW I was going to lose him. I could never shake the feeling. I never told anyone but he must have sensed it somehow. I look back at random text messages from his saying ‚ÄúI love you so much and will always be by your side‚Äù. He said things like that a LOT, maybe he felt something was tear us apart too. It‚Äôs been almost a decade, I never talk about him bc it just hurts to much. I‚Äôm a nice person and try to live a decent life but I was alone long before quarantine. I‚Äôve never dated anyone since he died, I‚Äôm scared to even have close friends. I see this tragedy caused by this woman and it hurts me. I think Johnny is probably a very kind ‚Äúevery day‚Äù person. Somehow this evil woman got into his life. Instead of treasuring the gift she had of a good person loving her, she made a mockery of marriage. She did all of this for no reason. If she didn‚Äôt want to be with him anymore I‚Äôm sure he would have been very generous toward her. It‚Äôs just so heartbreaking to see someone do these things to someone that really loves them. I‚Äôm glad he‚Äôs away from her and hope he can learn to trust again. Not specifically women, but just trust there is good in the world. He also uses gestures as if reliving it. He loses his phrasing and we see him trying to compose himself to remember. He looks upset when he‚Äôs stuttering, it‚Äôs not on purpose like with her.

This is so sad, and honestly an unsurprising reality for many abuse survivors. Dealing with such BS when you just want to be believed, just wanting it to be over even after you‚Äôve gotten away.   It‚Äôs incredible, and hopefully this case stays in people‚Äôs memories.
